                            SERVER CREATION

                        Basic Commands

                [1] Create package.json : npm init
                [2] Create Nodemodules : Install Express : npm i Express


                        Basic steps

                [1] Creating a folder : (BankServer)
                [2] Create a package.json file (npmm init)
                [3] Create a Nodemodules file (npm express)
                [4] Createindex.js file
                [5] Import express inside index.js
                [6] Create app using express
                [7] Set up port number
                [8] Resolving Http requests
                [9] Install nodemon : npm i -g nodemon
                [10] Http response code
                        1xx : Information
                        2xx : successful
                        3xx : Redirection
                        4xx : Client error
                        5xx : server error
                [11] JWt Token : Authentication
                        To check login or not?

                        login ---- token generate -----> Client --- req to deposit + token ----> server token check?
                        install JWT Token : jsonwebtoken

                                npm i jsonwebtoken

                                To generate a new JWT Token - sign()

                [12] middleware : To verify the token

                        It comes in the midlle of request and response
                        it also provides access to many functions

                        [a] Application-level middleware : for entire application
                        [b] Router-level middleware : to verify token

                                To validate the token : verify()

                [13] Database integration

                        [13.1] Install Mongoose : npm i mongoose (for connecting nodejs and mongodb)
                        [13.2] DB connect via mongoose 
                        [13.3] Create a model using mongoose

                [14] Asynchronous Function Resolving

                        [14.1] Resolving state : then()
                        [14.2] Rejection state : catch()

                [15] CORS : Cross origin resource sharing

                        